  "market_context": "Price had just swept a prior swing low (sell-side liquidity), then reversed upward. The analyst replayed the 5-minute ES chart to identify the valid bullish order block formed by the down-close candle that swept the low before the upward displacement.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst identified a large, full-bodied down-close candle that swept below the prior low as the valid bullish order block, rejecting smaller candles nearby due to their low probability structure.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst observed price sweeping a prior low (sell-side liquidity) and then moving back into the range, confirming a liquidity sweep and displacement setup.",
    "Step 2: The analyst located the down-close candle that swept the low immediately before the upward break of structure, identifying it as the bullish order block.",
    "Step 3: The analyst rejected a smaller nearby down-close candle as the OB, emphasizing preference for large full-bodied candles with small wicks as high-probability order blocks.",
    "Step 4: The analyst marked the OB zone (3904.50–3908.25) and noted price was supported there, leading to another leg up."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price was supported at the OB zone and produced another upward leg; no explicit trade entry/exit or P/L stated.",
  "lessons": "High-probability bullish order blocks are formed by large full-bodied down-close candles that sweep liquidity before an upward break of structure; use the opening price or mean threshold of that candle as the entry zone.",
